1. Explain the concept of e-commerce. Discuss the different features of e-commerce.

Ans.
The activity of purchasing, selling and exchange of goods and services, and information over the internet or any other form of electronic network is called E-Commerce. The central idea being – using digital technologies such as mobile or computer apps and websites etc. to enable interactions between B2B (Business to Business), B2C (Business to Consumer) and between government. Not only this, the idea also consists the use of internet to carry out electronic banking, e-ticketing, digital marketing etc. There are numerous benefits of e-commerce. The existence of e-commerce has helped companies to completely transform traditional business by removing geographic obstacles. This has enabled customers to take advantage of different choices, prices etc while companies reach global clients around the world. Over all, E-commerce promises on-time
delivery of products, services, safe payments etc. There are several methods of conducting E-commerce such as Amazon and Flipkart which deals in Business-to-Consumer (B2C). Alibaba deals in Business-to-Business (B2B), Ebay which deals in Consumer-to-Consumer (C2C) and several freelancing websites that deals in Consumer-to-Business (C2B).
There are several features of E-commerce which include -

a. User friendliness as while the companies have the control over their inventory and sales, customers on the other hand may browse, compare and purchase goods from the comfort of their homes.
b. Reduction in transaction charges – There is a reduction in operating costs as E- commerce enables automation and electronic payments etc.
c. Advanced encryption and authentication methods guarantee secure transactions and protect sensitive user data.
d. A global reach is ensured by E-commerce. This removes geographic boundaries thereby enabling business to cater to their customers all around the world.
